metadata.name: Flow of Life - Scars #1/33
metadata.description:
Scars

Life flows as a winding river,  
Through twists and turns we go,  
Scars we carry with us,  
Memories we'll never let go.

Some scars are deep and painful,  
Some fade with time and care,  
But all are part of the journey,  
That we walk through life with bare.

So let the river flow,  
Embrace the scars that come,  
For they are what make us,  
Who we are, and where we've come.
